{
  "texts": [
    "To translate predictions to discrete tumor response outcomes, we thresholded the AUC such that predictions below a value t low were labeled 'sensitive', those above a value t high were labeled 'resistant' and those between these two thresholds were labeled 'undefined' (Fig. 2a).",
    "At the most inclusive setting, t low = t high = median(AUC), NeST-VNN could accurately discriminate between actual sensitive and resistant cell lines in heldout test data, with a diagnostic odds ratio (OR) of 6.0.",
    "Discriminative power increased substantially with more stringent thresholds.",
    "For instance, setting the thresholds 1 s.d.",
    "from the median (t low, t high = median(AUC) ± s.d."
  ]
}